The paper deals with scheduling communication requests in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also takes into account the geometry of the network and power control, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of stochastic and adversarial models to bound packet injection is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses algorithms for scheduling problems, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.MA).
